body:
On the git master version. Using both `/* verilator public */` and `/* verilator forceable */` results in the force control signals to be created at the module level as `__PVT__` instead of public_flat.

```
module foo(
    input a /* verilator forceable */,
    input b,
    output c
    );

logic t1;

assign t1 = a & b;
assign c = t1;

endmodule

module bar(
    input x,
    input y,
    output z
    );

logic  t2 /* verilator public */;
logic t3;

foo u_foo(x, y, t3);

assign t2 = t3 | x;
assign z = t2;

endmodule
```

```
verilator --cc --top bar top.sv
```

